==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nearsightedness
<hw>Near"sight`ed*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
eyesight abnormality resulting from the eye's faulty refractive ability,
such that one can see only close objects distinctly; the condition of
being nearsighted. See <er>Myopic</er>, and <er>Myopia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> myopia, shortsightedness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neat</ent>⟦br⟧
